eq0$ then the above implies $|c^{3}-b-c|\geq b c^{2}-b-c.{\mathrm{~A s~}}b\geq c>1$ ,we must actually have $b=c.$ ,thus $a=c^{2}-1$ .Finally $a b-c=c(c^{2}-2)$ is a power of 2, hence $b=c=2,\mathrm{s o}a=3$ – In the second case, assume $c^{3}-b-c=0$ ,hence $c^{3}-c$ . From $b c-a=1$ we obtain $a=c^{4}-c^{2}-1$ , hence $$c a-b=c^{5}-2c^{3}=c^{3}(c^{2}-2)$$ is a power of 2, hence again $c=2$ . Thus $a=11$ and $b=6$ . This finishes all cases, so the proof is done.

